question:
What will be the output of the following code?

class Box {
    int width;
    Box(int w) { width = w; }
}

public class Test {
    static void modify(Box b) {
        b.width = b.width * 2;
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Box myBox = new Box(5);
        modify(myBox);
        System.out.println(myBox.width);
    }
}

Consider the code below. What is the value of `str` after `modifyString` is called?

public class Test {
    static void modifyString(String s) {
        s = s.concat(" World");
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String str = "Hello";
        modifyString(str);
        System.out.println(str);
    }
